data.value:
Preparation
• Stretch your core, hips, and back before starting.
• Find a flat, open space on the floor with a mat or soft surface for comfort.
• Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
• After pressing START, there’s a 4-second countdown before the challenge begins.
During the Challenge
• Lie on your back and place your hands behind your head, elbows wide.
• Lift your shoulders off the ground as you bring your right elbow toward your left knee.
• At the same time, extend your right leg straight, keeping it off the floor.
• Alternate sides, bringing your left elbow toward your right knee and extending your left leg.
• Keep your core engaged and focus on twisting your torso, not just moving your elbows.
• Maintain a steady pace for the entire 3 minutes.
• Press STOP or wait for the time to run out to return to the homepage.
Finishing the Challenge
• After 3 minutes, you’ll automatically be returned to the homepage.
Exercise Guide
• Start by lying flat on your back, knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
• Place your hands behind your head, elbows wide, and lift your shoulders off the ground.
• Twist your torso to bring your right elbow to your left knee while extending your right leg.
• Alternate sides in a slow and controlled manner, focusing on using your core to initiate the movement.
• Keep your lower back pressed into the floor and avoid pulling on your neck.
Note
Push yourself to maintain a controlled, steady pace for the full 3 minutes challenge. Focus on form and use your core muscles for each twist.
"Pedal your way to a stronger core with every crunch!"
